For riders, the police want to make sure the person on the train/plane isnt traveling with someone elses ID or hopping a train/plane to avoid police. Catching criminals in a real world crowd just with a glance.  In the last years, more and more wearable devices are being adapted for law enforcement. Next-generation wearables have the potential to enable police officers to improve situational awareness and decision making during missions. Law enforcement needs real-time information for better situational awareness in the field and at the command center. It is related to a more general concept called mediated reality, in which a view of reality is modified (possibly even diminished rather than augmented), by a computer. As a result, the technology functions by enhancing ones current perception of reality. By contrast, virtual reality replaces the real world with a simulated one. Virtualization is conventionally in real-time and in semantic context with environmental elements. Artificial information about the environment and its objects can be overlaid on the real world. node.name: rampUpApp
node.description: App Description: A 3D object placement app in which a user can place different types of ramps in 3D space anywhere he/she goes. Before placing these ramps, it is possible to see how they will appear by moving the ramps around in Ramp Picker View, picking it, placing it in Ramp Placer View, rotating it around, moving up & down, etc. in 3D environment within Augmented Reality. Here, when a user moves around, the app remembers the position of Ramp, thereby giving a feeling like it is actually there. Best part is, the app can be customized for any other type of 3D objects too.   Developed using Xcode 9 & Swift 4 for iOS 11 based devices.
